<strong>The three crucibles</strong>

<strong>Steel</strong> — Tier 1. 16-slot drum, 1600°C max, ~16 L molten capacity.
<strong>Adamantite</strong> — Tier 2. 32-slot drum, 2100°C max, ~32 L capacity.
<strong>Dragon</strong> — Tier 3. 64-slot drum, 2800°C max, ~64 L capacity. Only crucible that melts every metal.

<strong>Workflow</strong>
• Sneak + right-click a crucible to open its inventory. Load fuel in slot 0; ore in the cooking slots.
• The cook driver advances temperature ~25°C/sec while fuel burns. When every ingredient hits its melting point the crucible converts them to molten metal (single-metal smelt only — mixing rejected).
• Right-click hold on a crucible to tip the drum (the pouring gesture).
• Look at the block to see current temperature and molten contents.

<strong>Safeguards</strong>
Already-cooked items (ingots, already-melted forms) are refused at the cook stage. No ore lost to recook.

<strong>Reaching one tier higher</strong>
Attach a <a href="superheater">superheater</a> block to a large crucible for +300°C. Steel crucible reaches mithril; adamantite crucible reaches runite; dragon needs nothing.

<strong>Transport</strong>
Use the <a href="scoop">magma scoop</a> to move melt from one crucible to another.
